wdi-FP.CPI.TOTL.def: Consumer price index reflects changes in the cost to the average consumer of acquiring a basket of goods and services that may be fixed or changed at specified intervals, such as yearly. The Laspeyres formula is generally used. Data are period averages.
wdi-FP.CPI.TOTL.name: Consumer price index
wdi-FP.CPI.TOTL.source: International Monetary Fund, International Financial Statistics and data files.
